ith the letter <i>D-</i> (  compare  Jay   and   Kay  ), in particular   Dorothy .  It is also used as an independent name, and may in some cases be associated with the River Dee (  compare  Clyde  )."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705192,"age":6,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705193,"age":15,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705195,"age":60,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. John de Langton was born about 1322, in Leicestershire, England. She died from 9 January 1387 to 8 January 1388, in England."},"et":{"about 1322–1387":"umbes 1322–9. jaanuar 1387 kuni 8. jaanuar 1388","1322–1360":"1322–1360","1320–Male":"1320–Surnud","1329–Male":"1329–Surnud","1331–Male":"1331–Surnud","1340–1406":"1340–1406","–Male":"Surnud","1322–1387":"1322–9.jaanuar1387kuni8.jaanuar1388","1340":"1340","1360":"1360","1382":"1382","1337":"1337","about 1329":"umbes 1329","1322":"1322","1387":"9. jaanuar 1387 kuni 8. jaanuar 1388","1453":"1453","1331":"1331","1320":"1320","about 1322":"umbes 1322","about 1331":"umbes 1331","1406":"1406","1329":"1329","1328":"1